Comments:

Variable is the name of a memory location which stores some data.
Variables are case sensetive, like small v and Capital V are not same.
variable can only be charecter or underscore, no comma or blank space, no symbol is approved. 
it is recomended to name your variable in senseble name.

Code below :: number, star, age, pi, are variables and int, float, char are variable type:

CODE :


#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int number = 25;
    char star = ' * ';
    int age = 22;
    float pi = 3.14;
}
